Package sk.stu.fiit.projectBackend.exceptions

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    APIError
    APIError represents generic error which is returned to the user
    RestExceptionHandler  
  • Exception Summary
    Exception Description
    CartIsEmptyException
    CartIsEmptyException is thrown when the action doesn't allow empty cart
    EmailTakenException
    EmailTakenException is thrown when user wants to register with the email that somebody has used before
    IncorrectUsernameOrPasswordException
    IncorrectUsernameOrPasswordException is thrown when the user typed incorrect username or password
    InvalidRangeException
    InvalidRangeException is thrown when the user has provided value for variable which is out of range
    PermissionDeniedException
    PermissionDeniedException is thrown when the user has no permission for specific action
    RecordNotFoundException
    RecordNotFoundException is thrown when the searched record is not found
    TicketIsPurchased
    TicketIsPurchased is thrown when the user wants add Ticket to his cart that has been already purchased.
    TicketNotFoundException
    TicketNotFoundException is thrown when Ticket with specific ID is not found
    TicketPurchaseTimeExpiredException
    TicketPurchaseTimeExpiredException is thrown when user wants to perform some action upon ticket that lock's time has expired.
    TourDateNotFoundException
    TourDateNotFoundException is thrown when TourDate with specific ID is not found
    TourDateReservedException
    TourDateReservedException is thrown when user wants to delete TourDate for which somebody has already bought ticket
    TourOfferNotFoundException
    TourOfferNotFoundException is thrown when TourOffer with specific ID is not found
    UserNotFoundException
    UserNotFoundException is thrown when user with specific ID is not found
